\title{Nblm Flashcards}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.1.0}

\meta{trit}{1}

\meta{description}{"Generate and drill flashcards from NotebookLM Enterprise notebooks via Gemini (Vertex AI), with Emacs UI and babashka backfill pipeline"}

\subtree{
\title{NotebookLM Enterprise Flashcard Generator + Drill}
\p{\strong{Trit}: +1 (PLUS — knowledge extraction and spaced repetition from notebook sources)}

\subtree{
\title{What This Does}
\p{Extracts knowledge from the entire plurigrid/bmorphism ecosystem (1,244 repos across 5 NBLM notebooks) into drillable flashcards.}

\pre{\startverb
GitHub repos (1,244 total)
    |
    v
DeepWiki URLs → NBLM Enterprise (5 notebooks × 300 sources)
    |
    v
Discovery Engine API → fetch source titles
    |
    v
Gemini 2.5 Flash (Vertex AI) → batched generation
    |  5 sources/batch, 10 cards/source, token auto-refresh
    v
flashcards.json + quiz.json (per notebook)
    |
    v
bb n/nblm_merge.bb → all-flashcards.json (deduped)
    |
    v
Emacs drill (M-x nblm-drill-all)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Interaction with notebooklm-enterprise skill}
\p{This skill is the \strong{consumer} of notebooks managed by \code{\startverb notebooklm-enterprise\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
| notebooklm-enterprise (ERGODIC) | nblm-flashcards (PLUS) |
|----------------------------------|------------------------|
| Creates notebooks | Reads notebook sources |
| Adds DeepWiki URLs as sources | Generates flashcards from sources |
| Manages source ingestion status | Batches Gemini calls per source |
| Shares notebooks with users | Merges decks across notebooks |
\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Triad}
\pre{\startverb
notebooklm-enterprise (0) + nblm-flashcards (+1) + [verifier] (-1) = 0
\stopverb}

\p{The verifier role is filled by the Emacs drill itself — missed cards feed back as verification signal.}
}
}

